ENTRY            F0590   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0590001   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 10         29
TITLE      Levels of 28Si from the 24Mg(alpha,alpha)24Mg and
           24Mg(alpha,gamma)28Si reactions
AUTHOR     (J.Cseh,E.Koltay,Z.Mate,E.Somorjai,L.Zolnai)
INSTITUTE  (3HUNDEB)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,385,43,1982)
FACILITY   (VDG,3HUNDEB) 5 MeV Van de Graaff accelerator.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Six surface-barrier detectors were mounted at
           67.5, 80.5, 116.8, 134.7, 145.0, 162.5 degrees for
           measuring excitation function
           (NAICR) 8.cm * 8.cm NaI crystal was used to measure the
           gamma-ray excitation function simultaneously.
           (GELI) 70 cm3 and 25 cm3 Ge(Li) detectors (of 2.7 keV
           and 3.2 keV resolution at 1.33 MeV, respectively) were
           used to measure gamma-ray spectra and angular
           distribution.
SAMPLE     Targets of 4-9 keV thickness at Ea=3.5 MeV were
           prepared by vacuum evaporation of MgO, 98.5% enriched
           in 24Mg on thin self-supporting carbon foils.
ADD-RES    Multi-level R-matrix analysis was performed for
           nineteen resonances.
ERR-ANALYS (EN-ERR) The uncertainty of the absolute energy scale
           For energy calibration the Ealpha=3198.3 keV resonance
           was used (from P.M.Endt+,J,NP/A,310,1,1978)
HISTORY    (20030821C)
           (20110808A) SD: in Subent 003.1 - DATA: MEV -> KEV
           In Subent 002 angle 167.5 corrected on 162.5 - mistake
            on the figure 2 in the article.
           (20251216U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
           ANALYSIS -> ADD-RES.
ENDBIB              29
COMMON               1          3
EN-ERR
KEV
 5.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           36
SUBENT        F0590002   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  3          5
REACTION   (12-MG-24(A,EL)12-MG-24,,DA)
STATUS     (CURVE,,J.Cseh+,J,NP/A,385,43,1982) Fig.2
HISTORY    (20110808A) SD:angle 167.5 corrected on 162.5 - mistake
            on the figure 2 in the article.
           (20251216U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB               5
COMMON               2          3
EN-ERR-DIG ERR-DIG
MEV        B/SR
 0.0005     0.002
ENDCOMMON            3
